1.title: All About Wondrous Woman
1.plot: When Ratman launches a Super Shipping commercial that is actually an attack campaign because Wondrous Woman went to work for Stupendous Shipping, Stupendous Man wants to settle the score. This superhero parody spoofs Batman, Superman, Wonder Woman, Aquaman, and Spider-Man.

1.title: Pilot
1.plot: In this first episode of Super Shipping, Ocean Man tries to interview for a position in Ratman's new superhero international shipping business but is met with only insults before being thrown out. Features spoofs of Batman, Aquaman, Wonder Woman, Flash, and Spider-Man.

4.title: Mother's Day
4.plot: Wondrous Woman isn't happy about Ratman working our Super Shippers on Mother's Day. Things get hysterical when Moley Cyrus tries to take revenge on them with a wrecking ball. This superhero spoof moves past parodies of Batman, Wonder Woman, Spiderman, and other Marvel and DC superheroes to icons like Justin Bieber and Miley Cyrus. No one is safe in this parody series that.

5.title: Importing a Superhero
5.plot: Super Shipping HQ is hilariously dysfunctional as Sticky-Man tries to stop Ratman from hiring a replacement for Wondrous Woman. Features spoofs of Green Lantern, Catwoman, Batman, Spider-Man, Wonder Woman, Aquaman, and a guest appearance by Youtube celebrity Nalts.

6.title: Best Pick Up Lines
6.plot: When Wondrous Woman joins Stupendous Shipping after leaving Super Shipping, she gives Ocean Man one opportunity to get all of his best pick up lines out of his system. In the process, a secret is uncovered. Features spoofs of Wonder Woman, Aquaman, and Superman.

imdb.plot outline: Everything seems to be going wrong for Ratman and his international shipping company staffed entirely with superheroes. Streak, with his super speed, constantly struggles with costume malfunctions as he's supposed to be delivering ocean freight. Wondrous Woman keeps losing her invisible jet full of air cargo. And Sticky-Man proves that with great stickiness comes great incompetence. Worst of all, Ocean-Man is teaming up with Stupendous-Man with the goal of putting Super Shipping out of business.
